nt|^z@3^b@2
There is some useful terminology that will make it easier for us to discuss bidding. As we have seen, the first non-pass in the bidding is referred to as the opening bid.|
pg| ***** 57 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2
The player that makes the opening bid is known as the opening bidder (or simply the opener) and his partner is known as the responder. Here South's 1@C makes him the opening bidder and his partner, North, becomes the responder.|
