ht|f|n^|5|at|^k{|ih|psKt5HA8DK954CAJ63|at|}

^^Do not open 1@D because you have 4-4 in the minors. This hand is a perfect 1NT opening bid. There are 15 HCP in this hand, just enough for 1NT, and the hand is certainly balanced, having just 1 doubleton. It is nice that there are stoppers in all 4 suits, but this is not a requirement for a 1NT opening bid. Do not open 1NT with the 2 hands below, use the other rules instead:
|
