pg| ***** 374 ***** |


at|In each definition there are not enough total points for a 1-level opening bid. The higher the level of the preempt, the more cards that are required in the long suit. A weak 2-bid requires a 6-card suit, while 3 and 4-level opening preempts require 7-card and 8-card suits respectively.

|
pg| ***** 375 ***** |


at|Also note that all of our preemptive openings must be based on a strong suit. There are various definitions of what constitutes a strong suit, but the definition we will use is as follows:

|cs|1|at|^-{A strong suit contains at least 2 of the top 3 cards (the Ace, King, and Queen).}
|
